00:18:11,720 --> 00:18:14,320
Even though I might end up
losing everything.

273
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:16,360
At least,

274
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:20,200
I've tried and succeeded.

275
00:18:20,960 --> 00:18:22,240
You're my son.

276
00:18:22,920 --> 00:18:24,920
Don't disappoint me

277
00:18:25,200 --> 00:18:27,560
by aimlessly wandering through life.

278
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:45,920
Xia Lin should act
in more dramas with this genre.

279
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:47,680
-I understand, sir.
-Got it?

280
00:18:47,840 --> 00:18:49,960
-Promote your artists.
-Okay.

281
00:18:50,040 --> 00:18:51,560
-Okay?
-Okay.

282
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:59,680
Here are the clothes. Good job today.

283
00:18:59,800 --> 00:19:01,160
Of course. You too.

284
00:19:01,240 --> 00:19:04,560
By the way, what brand is the tie
that the male lead wore today?

285
00:19:04,640 --> 00:19:05,640
It looked nice.

286
00:19:05,720 --> 00:19:08,200
Are you noticing these details
now that you two are living together?

287
00:19:08,760 --> 00:19:11,520
I'll send the store's address to you later
and you can browse directly.

288
00:19:11,680 --> 00:19:13,560
-Okay. Thank you.
-I'm taking off now.

289
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:15,400
-Don't forget your bag.
-Thank you.

290
00:19:17,760 --> 00:19:18,600
Ms. Jiang.

291
00:19:19,040 --> 00:19:20,120
What's this about?

292
00:19:20,440 --> 00:19:21,840
LING YIZHOU MOVES IN WITH XIA LIN,
BECOMES HOMEMAKER FOR LOVE

293
00:19:23,960 --> 00:19:25,920
It happened quite unexpectedly.

294
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:27,560
Wait a minute.

295
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:31,520
<i>Ms. Xia, Boss is drunk.</i>

296
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:33,720
-<i>Could you please come by?</i>
-I...

297
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:35,840
Ms. Jiang, I have to take care
of something urgent.

298
00:19:35,920 --> 00:19:36,840
Help me fix that.

299
00:19:36,920 --> 00:19:38,480
I'll explain it next time.

300
00:19:38,560 --> 00:19:39,400
-You...
-Bye!

301
00:19:39,480 --> 00:19:40,480
Where are you going?

302
00:19:40,560 --> 00:19:42,080
I just have to leave!

303
00:19:51,200 --> 00:19:52,680
Where is he?

304
00:19:56,320 --> 00:19:57,840
Mr. Wen, I'm here.

305
00:19:57,920 --> 00:19:59,720
Where are you? Why can't I see you?

306
00:20:08,560 --> 00:20:09,760
Boss, are you okay?

307
00:20:09,920 --> 00:20:11,600
What happened? Why is he so drunk?

308
00:20:11,680 --> 00:20:13,520
The company's crisis
was handled successfully.

309
00:20:13,720 --> 00:20:15,960
-He was in a happy mood and overindulged.
-Look!

310
00:20:17,360 --> 00:20:19,280
It's a building!

311
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:21,160
-Yes, it's a building.
-Yes, you're right.

312
00:20:21,280 --> 00:20:22,760
Leave him to me. Don't worry about him.

313
00:20:23,840 --> 00:20:25,800
-That's light!
-You should head home.

314
00:20:25,880 --> 00:20:26,840
I'll take Mr. Cheng home.

315
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:27,960
-Go on.
-Be careful.

316
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:29,320
Watch out.

317
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:33,280
-An airplane.
-All right. Are you okay?

318
00:20:35,280 --> 00:20:36,160
Are you all right?

319
00:20:37,040 --> 00:20:38,000
I'm okay.

320
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:40,720
Hey! Be careful.

321
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:42,480
Why did you drink so much?

322
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:52,360
Hey, be careful.

323
00:20:52,560 --> 00:20:54,280
Slowly.

324
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:55,920
Let me help you.

325
00:20:56,240 --> 00:20:57,600
Let me help you.

326
00:20:59,680 --> 00:21:00,720
All right.

327
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:03,480
Aren't we going home?

328
00:21:03,560 --> 00:21:05,920
Yes, we're going home now.

329
00:21:12,280 --> 00:21:13,360
What's wrong?

330
00:21:17,960 --> 00:21:19,360
Where's the steering wheel?

331
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:25,960
Have you seen my steering wheel?

332
00:21:26,880 --> 00:21:28,640
Where's your steering wheel?

333
00:21:28,760 --> 00:21:29,880
I need to drive home.

334
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:32,160
I need the steering wheel to do that.

335
00:21:32,240 --> 00:21:35,000
-Where's my steering wheel?
-The wheel is right in front of you.

336
00:21:35,120 --> 00:21:36,440
Just reach out.

337
00:21:36,680 --> 00:21:38,880
Do you see it? It's right in front of you.

338
00:21:40,800 --> 00:21:43,640
-Yes, right there.
-Here it is.

339
00:21:44,640 --> 00:21:47,160
Hold it and you can drive.

340
00:21:47,280 --> 00:21:48,920
I know how to drive.

341
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:54,600
I'll be going now.

342
00:21:55,040 --> 00:21:56,400
Drive safely.

343
00:22:22,320 --> 00:22:24,600
Why are you outside my house?

344
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:27,320
Well, I...

345
00:22:27,400 --> 00:22:28,880
Never mind. It's okay.

346
00:22:29,120 --> 00:22:30,280
Get in.

347
00:22:30,480 --> 00:22:31,520
I'll drive you home.

348
00:22:31,640 --> 00:22:33,640
Okay, I'm coming.

349
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:46,240
Right.

350
00:22:48,680 --> 00:22:49,640
I'll help you with that.

351
00:22:50,360 --> 00:22:51,360
Okay.

352
00:23:27,320 --> 00:23:28,600
Don't move.

353
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:32,120
Why did you drink so much?

354
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:34,600
Ling Yizhou, we're home.

355
00:23:39,320 --> 00:23:40,240
Come on.

356
00:23:42,320 --> 00:23:43,240
Let's go.

357
00:23:44,080 --> 00:23:46,400
Why did you have to drink so much?

358
00:23:48,920 --> 00:23:49,840
Careful.

359
00:23:50,960 --> 00:23:51,920
Slow down.

360
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:02,880
<i>So it's true.</i>

361
00:24:09,280 --> 00:24:10,240
Careful.

362
00:24:17,240 --> 00:24:18,440
Watch out.

363
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:29,680
Gosh, I'm exhausted.

364
00:24:30,080 --> 00:24:31,560
You're heavier than you look.

365
00:24:32,240 --> 00:24:33,600
Feeling nauseous?

366
00:24:34,080 --> 00:24:35,240
Serves you right.

367
00:24:36,400 --> 00:24:37,440
Jeez,

368
00:24:37,960 --> 00:24:39,440
you drank so much.

369
00:24:39,880 --> 00:24:41,600
You brought this upon yourself.

370
00:24:43,160 --> 00:24:44,160
Turn over.

371
00:24:44,720 --> 00:24:46,320
You're so heavy.

372
00:24:49,400 --> 00:24:51,320
This side now.

373
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:55,400
This is tiring.

374
00:25:00,640 --> 00:25:01,960
What are you doing?

375
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:03,400
What, Mumu?

376
00:25:04,040 --> 00:25:05,120
I'm warning you.

377
00:25:05,720 --> 00:25:06,760
Since you're drunk,

378
00:25:06,840 --> 00:25:08,400
I'm afraid I won't be able
to control myself.

379
00:25:08,480 --> 00:25:10,000
I might take advantage of you.

380
00:25:12,440 --> 00:25:14,120
That got your attention?

381
00:25:14,360 --> 00:25:15,320
Are you sober now?

382
00:25:16,480 --> 00:25:17,640
No.

383
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:48,760
Ling Yizhou, you're drunk.

384
00:25:49,160 --> 00:25:51,240
I'll get a towel for you
so you can cool down.

385
00:25:58,440 --> 00:25:59,680
Xia Lin.

386
00:25:59,920 --> 00:26:01,120
You're the one to talk.

387
00:26:01,280 --> 00:26:03,480
You're the one who needs to calm down!
What are you doing?

388
00:26:04,080 --> 00:26:05,680
<i>Aren't you two engaged?</i>

389
00:26:06,040 --> 00:26:07,040
What's done is done.

390
00:26:07,160 --> 00:26:08,920
It's past the point of no return.

391
00:26:09,680 --> 00:26:10,760
But, I...

392
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:13,680
But it's a fake engagement.

393
00:26:13,800 --> 00:26:16,320
Aren't those just excuses?

394
00:26:39,880 --> 00:26:41,080
Ling Yizhou?

395
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:43,040
Ling Yizhou?

396
00:27:24,360 --> 00:27:25,600
Good night.

397
00:29:27,400 --> 00:29:30,320
<i>Boss, Mr. Chu had
a sudden heart attack last night</i>

398
00:29:30,400 --> 00:29:31,240
<i>and was hospitalized.</i>

399
00:29:31,320 --> 00:29:33,400
<i>He is stable now but needs to rest.</i>

400
00:29:48,320 --> 00:29:49,600
OUTPATIENT

401
00:29:49,720 --> 00:29:52,000
Mr. Chu, how are you feeling?

402
00:29:52,480 --> 00:29:54,200
Old man, I brought food for you.

403
00:29:56,360 --> 00:29:57,320
Yizhou?

404
00:29:57,680 --> 00:29:58,560
Why are you here?

405
00:29:59,040 --> 00:30:01,040
I came to see how your dad is doing.

406
00:30:01,160 --> 00:30:02,640
I'm glad he's fine.

407
00:30:03,640 --> 00:30:04,760
You should get going.

408
00:30:04,840 --> 00:30:05,960
You came so early.

409
00:30:06,120 --> 00:30:07,960
I'm sure you're needed at your company.

410
00:30:08,040 --> 00:30:09,520
Go back to work.

411
00:30:09,640 --> 00:30:11,480
Mr. Chu, I'll be leaving now then.

412
00:30:11,680 --> 00:30:13,760
I'll give my grandma an update later.

413
00:30:13,840 --> 00:30:15,440
Don't alarm her.

414
00:30:15,520 --> 00:30:17,280
-Tell her not to worry.
-Okay.

415
00:30:17,480 --> 00:30:19,240
-I'll visit her after I'm discharged.
-Okay.

416
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:20,840
-Good.
-Take care.

417
00:30:21,560 --> 00:30:22,520
Goodbye.

418
00:30:22,880 --> 00:30:24,400
I'll see him out.

419
00:30:32,640 --> 00:30:34,320
I heard about your dad's company.

420
00:30:34,440 --> 00:30:35,760
Is there anything I can help with?

421
00:30:36,520 --> 00:30:37,440
No.

422
00:30:37,840 --> 00:30:39,360
I've decided to return to the company.

423
00:30:39,920 --> 00:30:41,120
Are you going to quit acting?

424
00:30:42,680 --> 00:30:45,840
I plan on retiring
after wrapping up my current drama.

425
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:48,280
You're giving up already?

426
00:30:48,600 --> 00:30:49,640
That's not like you.

427
00:30:50,720 --> 00:30:51,840
I'm not giving up.

428
00:30:52,320 --> 00:30:55,600
I just came to the realization

429
00:30:56,160 --> 00:30:57,640
that I want to be there for my loved ones

430
00:30:58,040 --> 00:31:00,080
when they are sick or dying.

431
00:31:00,160 --> 00:31:01,080
Hey.

432
00:31:01,280 --> 00:31:02,560
Don't try to comfort me.

433
00:31:03,520 --> 00:31:05,360
My dad and I have been at odds for years.

434
00:31:05,960 --> 00:31:07,840
It suddenly feels pointless.

435
00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:09,320
And lately,

436
00:31:09,760 --> 00:31:11,600
I realized I don't like acting very much.

437
00:31:12,280 --> 00:31:13,960
I'm going to try a different career.

438
00:31:15,960 --> 00:31:17,760
I thought you loved acting.

439
00:31:18,920 --> 00:31:20,000
It's all right.

440
00:31:20,680 --> 00:31:22,200
Do you remember that when we met,

441
00:31:23,320 --> 00:31:24,480
I was really into photography?

442
00:31:25,120 --> 00:31:26,720
I wanted to be
a professional photographer.

443
00:31:27,520 --> 00:31:30,400
I somehow became an actor
and discovered I had some talent.

444
00:31:30,520 --> 00:31:31,760
So I continued down that path.

445
00:31:33,320 --> 00:31:34,520
If that's the case,

446
00:31:35,320 --> 00:31:37,720
have you considered
integrating acting and photography

447
00:31:38,400 --> 00:31:41,200
into your company's operations?

448
00:31:41,280 --> 00:31:42,240
Are you kidding me?

449
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:43,480
You already have an idea?

450
00:31:44,320 --> 00:31:45,400
I mean...

451
00:31:46,640 --> 00:31:48,640
Take over the company first
and get a lay of the land.

452
00:31:48,720 --> 00:31:49,880
See if there's any overlap.

453
00:31:50,320 --> 00:31:52,280
Don't hesitate to ask for help.

454
00:31:54,200 --> 00:31:56,200
All right, I'll give it a try.

455
00:31:56,680 --> 00:31:58,600
We're not out of options yet.

456
00:31:58,680 --> 00:31:59,840
Besides, my dad said

457
00:32:00,360 --> 00:32:02,320
no matter how bad it gets,

458
00:32:02,400 --> 00:32:03,800
we still won't be homeless.

459
00:32:07,640 --> 00:32:08,520
Right.

460
00:32:11,840 --> 00:32:13,680
I saw you and Xia Lin yesterday

461
00:32:14,320 --> 00:32:15,240
outside her place.

462
00:32:23,920 --> 00:32:24,840
Ling Yizhou.

463
00:32:25,400 --> 00:32:26,880
Xia Lin is a good girl.

464
00:32:27,360 --> 00:32:31,040
She has been giving her best
ever since she entered the industry.

465
00:32:39,080 --> 00:32:40,640
I never confessed my feelings to her.

466
00:32:42,040 --> 00:32:43,760
That's because I didn't know

467
00:32:43,840 --> 00:32:45,920
whether my feelings for her

468
00:32:46,360 --> 00:32:48,360
were as a friend, a lover,

469
00:32:48,960 --> 00:32:50,440
or a colleague.

470
00:32:51,400 --> 00:32:53,400
Either way, all this time,

471
00:32:53,800 --> 00:32:56,480
I've been quietly watching over her
as a friend.

472
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:00,080
She's not a flower
that needs to be sheltered.

473
00:33:02,280 --> 00:33:04,160
Still, I have to thank you.

474
00:33:04,920 --> 00:33:09,640
Thank you for being at her side
as a friend.

475
00:33:12,920 --> 00:33:14,200
Don't be so smug.

476
00:33:14,640 --> 00:33:15,520
I'm warning you.

477
00:33:15,720 --> 00:33:17,320
If you don't treat her well,

478
00:33:17,400 --> 00:33:18,720
-I will--
-You'll what?

479
00:33:18,800 --> 00:33:21,640
I won't give you
a snowball's chance in hell.

480
00:33:21,880 --> 00:33:23,600
Don't think about getting between us.

481
00:33:25,040 --> 00:33:26,200
While we're acting,

482
00:33:26,280 --> 00:33:28,320
she and I could still be a couple.

483
00:33:28,520 --> 00:33:29,960
-Really?
-Pidan could be our child.

484
00:34:13,600 --> 00:34:15,840
<i>Mumu, I need to go out for a bit.</i>

485
00:34:15,920 --> 00:34:16,960
<i>Let's have dinner together.</i>

486
00:34:17,440 --> 00:34:18,639
<i>Thanks for your help last night.</i>

487
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:19,960
<i>Ling Yizhou.</i>

488
00:34:40,320 --> 00:34:42,880
<i>Having fun living together?</i>

489
00:34:43,600 --> 00:34:45,320
<i>It happened out of the blue.</i>

490
00:34:45,480 --> 00:34:47,600
<i>I'm totally devastated.</i>

491
00:34:52,920 --> 00:34:54,120
<i>Are you free today?</i>

492
00:34:54,480 --> 00:34:56,920
<i>Come out and I'll take your mind off it.</i>

493
00:34:57,800 --> 00:34:58,920
<i>Yes, ma'am!</i>

494
00:34:59,560 --> 00:35:02,480
<i>I have something to ask you anyway.</i>

495
00:35:23,760 --> 00:35:24,840
JIA FEI

496
00:35:24,920 --> 00:35:26,600
IT HAS BEEN SO LONG
SINCE I'VE WORKED UP A SWEAT.

497
00:35:26,680 --> 00:35:28,240
I'M STILL KILLING IT!

498
00:35:33,760 --> 00:35:35,200
<i>I'm leaving work soon. Where are you?</i>

499
00:35:35,280 --> 00:35:36,360
<i>Should I pick you up?</i>

500
00:35:37,400 --> 00:35:39,600
LINGSHI GROUP

501
00:35:39,920 --> 00:35:42,360
<i>No need. I'm out with Linlin.</i>

502
00:35:45,040 --> 00:35:47,920
Queenie, make the changes
that I just mentioned.

503
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:49,040
Okay, Mr. Ling.

504
00:35:49,600 --> 00:35:50,440
Boss!

505
00:35:51,240 --> 00:35:52,160
You can go now.

506
00:35:52,240 --> 00:35:53,760
LINGSHI GROUP

507
00:35:54,120 --> 00:35:55,440
The boss said you can go now.

508
00:35:57,320 --> 00:35:58,200
Wen Li.

509
00:35:59,320 --> 00:36:01,560
Grab a few things from my house
and take them to Mumu's.

510
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:02,920
Okay.

511
00:36:04,880 --> 00:36:05,880
Why aren't you going?

512
00:36:06,200 --> 00:36:08,240
I'll go.

513
00:36:09,800 --> 00:36:10,960
Is something the matter?

514
00:36:11,480 --> 00:36:12,960
Ms. Xia and Jia Fei

515
00:36:13,520 --> 00:36:15,040
might not be home.

516
00:36:20,920 --> 00:36:22,600
-I'm going.
-Where are you going?

517
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:23,880
To the gym!

518
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:36,320
Did Wen Li tell you?

519
00:36:37,400 --> 00:36:40,080
I learned from the general public.

520
00:36:41,360 --> 00:36:43,640
So what do you think?

521
00:36:43,880 --> 00:36:46,400
It's already clear that
Mr. Ling likes you.

522
00:36:47,800 --> 00:36:48,880
But...

523
00:36:49,080 --> 00:36:50,760
-Enough buts.
-But...

524
00:36:54,960 --> 00:36:55,920
See for yourself.

525
00:36:56,200 --> 00:36:58,680
Look at that silly grin on his face.

526
00:36:59,800 --> 00:37:03,000
It's confirmed that he likes you.

527
00:37:03,320 --> 00:37:06,560
What matters now is what you think.

528
00:37:06,680 --> 00:37:07,680
I...

529
00:37:08,720 --> 00:37:10,680
I don't know.

530
00:37:12,440 --> 00:37:14,400
Xia Lin, look.

531
00:37:15,320 --> 00:37:17,800
Based on my experience as a screenwriter,

532
00:37:18,480 --> 00:37:20,760
there's no running away for you.

533
00:37:22,840 --> 00:37:23,760
What?

534
00:37:24,080 --> 00:37:28,080
You can't escape from Mr. Ling's clutches.

535
00:37:35,200 --> 00:37:37,800
For my script, I've recently been studying

536
00:37:38,040 --> 00:37:40,040
relationships in which the woman
is older than the man.

537
00:37:40,160 --> 00:37:45,400
My male lead is a testosterone-fueled hunk
who is clingy like a puppy.

538
00:37:45,920 --> 00:37:48,000
This is the perfect opportunity...

539
00:37:49,880 --> 00:37:51,760
to do some research.

540
00:37:56,880 --> 00:37:58,440
Why do I get the feeling

541
00:37:59,360 --> 00:38:00,600
research

542
00:38:01,480 --> 00:38:03,120
is just an excuse?

543
00:38:42,240 --> 00:38:45,680
<i>Don't tell me those two are going to...</i>

